    • Method Detail

      • read

        public java.nio.ByteBuffer read(NativeProcess process,
                                int offset,
                                int bytesToRead)
        Reads the specified amount of bytes from the specified offset at the native process' memory.

        This implementation is largely implemented on top of the Windows API. First, a handle is opened to the target process, then the memory is read with the Kernel32 ReadProcessMemory function.

        Specified by:
        read in interface RawMemoryReader
        Parameters:
        process - the native process whose memory will be read.
        offset - the memory address offset to read from. This value is interpreted as an unsigned value, meaning that negative values are allowed.
        bytesToRead - the amount of bytes to read.
        Returns:
        the read bytes.
        Throws:
        ProcessOpenException - if a handle for the specified process cannot be opened.
